chrome_web_navigation

Top-Level Variables
web_navigation: ChromeWebNavigation
Classes
ChromeWebNavigation

Use the chrome.webNavigation API to receive notifications about the status of navigation requests in-flight.

Top-Level Variables

static final ChromeWebNavigation web_navigation

Getters and Setters

Stream<dynamic> get onBeforeNavigate

Fired when a navigation is about to occur.

Stream<dynamic> get onCommitted

Fired when a navigation is committed. The document (and the resources it refers to, such as images and subframes) might still be downloading, but at least part of the document has been received from the server and the browser has decided to switch to the new document.

Stream<dynamic> get onCompleted

Fired when a document, including the resources it refers to, is completely loaded and initialized.

Stream<dynamic> get onCreatedNavigationTarget

Fired when a new window, or a new tab in an existing window, is created to host a navigation.

Stream<dynamic> get onDOMContentLoaded

Fired when the page's DOM is fully constructed, but the referenced resources may not finish loading.

Stream<dynamic> get onErrorOccurred

Fired when an error occurs and the navigation is aborted. This can happen if either a network error occurred, or the user aborted the navigation.

Stream<dynamic> get onHistoryStateUpdated

Fired when the frame's history was updated to a new URL. All future events for that frame will use the updated URL.

Stream<dynamic> get onReferenceFragmentUpdated

Fired when the reference fragment of a frame was updated. All future events for that frame will use the updated URL.

Stream<dynamic> get onTabReplaced

Fired when the contents of the tab is replaced by a different (usually previously pre-rendered) tab.

Methods

void getAllFrames(dynamic details, dynamic callback)

Retrieves information about all frames of a given tab. details Information about the tab to retrieve all frames from.

void getFrame(dynamic details, dynamic callback)

Retrieves information about the given frame. A frame refers to an &lt;iframe&gt; or a &lt;frame&gt; of a web page and is identified by a tab ID and a frame ID. details Information about the frame to retrieve information about.
